Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.85,0:00:04.73,sign_69_1_One_Strike,Text,0000,0000,0000,,One Strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.34,0:00:04.73,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,One strike...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.90,0:00:11.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,It's necessary to hit the enemy's \Nvital point in one strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.87,0:00:14.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,You suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.47,0:00:16.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.51,0:00:20.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.53,0:00:23.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,Writing a letter to a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.94,0:01:58.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Load all the cargo from my \Ncountry into hatch number three!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.93,0:02:00.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Damage anything, and you pay for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:03.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:06.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Why must I direct the loading of cargo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.67,0:02:18.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:19.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:22.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Your gaze is such a nuisance, \NI can't hear the voice of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.86,0:02:27.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so? What a pious minister you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.34,0:02:30.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm sure you must love this verse...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.53,0:02:32.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,"Dust to dust."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.87,0:02:43.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Genesis 3:19.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.63,0:02:45.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,While everyone else is \Nscattered upon the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:48.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,it's our duty to protect this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.51,0:02:50.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.05,0:02:54.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you aren't\Nthe one who has forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.41,0:02:59.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,It is my sacred duty to \Npass judgment on sinners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.68,0:03:02.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Any number of enemies is \Nwelcome to come at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.28,0:03:08.20,sign_4383_26_Guild_Operative_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Guild Operative\N Nathaniel H.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.38,0:03:06.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,They will atone for their \Nsins with their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:08.20,sign_4450_27_Ability___The_Sc,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Ability: \NThe Scarlet Letter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:10.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you wish for atonement as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.45,0:03:14.63,sign_4529_30_Guild_Operative_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Guild Apprentice\NMargaret M.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:14.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't even worthy of polishing my shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.46,0:03:14.63,sign_4599_31_Ability___Gone_w,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Ability: \NGone with the Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:17.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Excuse me—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:22.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This letter was found among the cargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.76,0:03:24.05,sign_4790_34_Dear_Guild,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Guild
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:23.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:29.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Sir and Madam...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.40,0:03:35.40,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,I hope this letter finds \Nyou in the best of health.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:37.57,Stray Dogs - Top,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,Rintarou, you jerk! Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.06,0:03:38.15,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,I write regarding the \Nrecent military conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.15,0:03:39.61,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,While it may sound presumptuous,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:44.24,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to inform you of the Guild \Nassets that we will next obliterate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.66,0:03:44.24,Stray Dogs - Top,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my crayon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:48.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,"These are the guild assets that \Nwe will next obliterate..."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:54.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,"First, your luxury liner, the Zelda.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.94,0:03:58.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Second, the life of Mr. Nathaniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.48,0:04:01.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Third, the life of Ms. Margaret."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:02.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.73,0:04:06.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,"Sincerely, Mori Ougai, \NBoss of the Port Mafia."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.65,0:04:09.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Obliterate us and the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:10.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:14.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We'll depart once all cargo is on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:16.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,How long?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:18.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,About two more hours, I believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.27,0:04:19.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Get it done in thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:21.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty minutes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.05,0:04:22.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,You can have the freight helicopter unload
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:26.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,on the deck helipad while the \Nregular loading is going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.47,0:04:29.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,And strengthen security around the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:30.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.76,0:04:33.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,This silly threat letter is just a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:35.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.07,0:04:39.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Given that our Guild has no base on land,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:41.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,this ship is essentially our front-line base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.75,0:04:43.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.04,0:04:47.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,This moment, as we're replenishing \Nsupplies, is when we're most vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.02,0:04:51.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Our enemy, this supernatural organization, \Nmay not be a threat to our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.08,0:04:55.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,but should they launch a surprise \Nattack, they could sink this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:57.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Nathaniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.52,0:05:04.03,Stray Dogs Ep Title,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Eighteen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.01,0:05:02.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We've found a suspicious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.28,0:05:07.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He was found on the pier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.94,0:05:10.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He tried to escape, so we restrained him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.89,0:05:12.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He was carrying this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.16,0:05:16.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,He's just a thug from some island nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:19.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,I saw your face pictured in a report,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.52,0:05:21.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Port Mafia Bomber.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.82,0:05:25.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, who am I? Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.03,0:05:30.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you once attempted to bomb a train, \Nbut were stopped by the Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.22,0:05:31.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,That was an experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.55,0:05:33.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,Every failure is a valuable sample!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:36.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I make a mummy out of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.59,0:05:40.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,No, I already have a good \Nidea of the enemy's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.15,0:05:43.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,He was, no doubt, in charge \Nof planting a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.15,0:05:45.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,What a shoddy organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.35,0:05:50.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,His blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.17,0:05:52.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,The Scarlet Letter is the Word of God...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.01,0:05:57.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,A judgment ability that penalizes the immoral\Nand leaves on them a mark that never fades.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.33,0:05:57.84,Stray Dogs - Top,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.84,0:06:00.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay, I get it! I surrender! \NI'll tell you everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:03.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I'm an ambassador representing \Nthe commander-in-chief of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:06.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,If you hurt me, you'll be in real trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.97,0:06:06.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.71,0:06:11.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.95,0:06:14.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,you refuse to repent and atone for your sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.05,0:06:19.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,These lemon-shaped bombs are your ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.69,0:06:21.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,How truly foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:24.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Even a common man can make bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.82,0:06:29.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,You thought you could sink this \Nship with an ability like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:32.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,You've obviously underestimated the Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.72,0:06:39.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,May God's grace be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.10,0:06:44.21,Stray Dogs - Italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We will now unload the \Nsupplies onto the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.56,0:06:49.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,God... God, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:53.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you can hear the voice of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.14,0:06:59.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,Science is the only language that allows us to\N understand this universe God created.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.55,0:07:02.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,The explosion didn't affect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.20,0:07:04.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,I have bad news for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:08.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,It's the job of you clergymen to believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:11.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,but the very foundation of science \Nis to question everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.56,0:07:16.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,You should have questioned this \Nbomb-making ability a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.56,0:07:20.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,It is true that I made these\N bombs on my own time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.99,0:07:25.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,And my true gift is the ability to take \Nno damage from lemon-shaped bombs!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:29.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,Lemons! That beautiful spindle \Nshape is the ultimate geometry,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.52,0:07:31.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the destroyer \Nof this tedious world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:34.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,On that note, here's a present for you from
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.44,0:07:36.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Kajii,0000,0000,0000,,the commander-in-chief\Nof the universe and myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.27,0:07:39.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:44.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone get away from the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.29,0:08:04.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,The ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:06.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,Just who is that man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.62,0:08:09.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,It appears the threat \Nletter was no mere prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.69,0:08:14.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,And two targets still remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.33,0:08:18.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy will be upon us shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.82,0:08:20.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,We will engage them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:22.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,If we stop their surprise attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.37,0:08:26.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,no number of gifted enemies \Ncan be a match for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.65,0:08:30.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,...is probably what our enemy will think.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.58,0:08:34.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild's gifted members \Nare indeed formidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.74,0:08:38.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,Even our elite would have a \Ndifficult time bringing them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.25,0:08:42.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.45,0:08:49.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,I've just played my most \Neager, motivated piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,This sea breeze is suffocating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.14,0:09:16.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get this over with quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.32,0:09:20.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a Port Mafia assassin?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.77,0:09:23.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling, irmão of the Guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.47,0:09:24.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.81,0:09:28.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,A bit like I've had a run-in with \Nthe devil spoken of in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:30.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.32,0:09:33.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Diablo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.87,0:09:37.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Then this must be Mount Hermon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.65,0:09:41.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a trial sent to test this \Nhumble servant's faith in God?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.56,0:09:43.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a trial you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.52,0:09:45.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll give you one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.12,0:09:51.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Do not call me "irmão."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.76,0:09:55.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,I am a minister, not some \Nrelic of ancient Rome!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.71,0:09:58.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that will be \Nenough to test my faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.86,0:10:00.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,you trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.88,0:10:05.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Repent, little guy of the Port Mafia!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:07.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:14.69,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy's ability is intermediate-range \Nmatter manipulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.69,0:10:17.22,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathanial,0000,0000,0000,,both offensive and defensive?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.53,0:10:19.85,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,That's similar to my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:21.60,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:26.06,Stray Dogs - Italics,Both,0000,0000,0000,,The one whose ability holds \Nthe most potential will win!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:28.14,sign_15027_153_Rashoumon,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Rashoumon
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.98,0:10:28.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Rashoumon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:31.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,The Scarlet Letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.02,0:10:32.23,sign_15130_155_The_Scarlet_Lett,Text,0000,0000,0000,,The Scarlet Letter
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.59,0:10:39.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you can do, irmão?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:46.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,You are no devil at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:47.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:51.83,Stray Dogs - Italics,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,The blood on my coat is turning into writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.05,0:10:57.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,You are merely a soulless beast \Nthat craves the flesh of the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.12,0:11:01.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've only fought gifted enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.45,0:11:03.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,who were weaker than you up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.45,0:11:08.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,The Port Mafia is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.92,0:11:11.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,I will take back my family's honor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:17.19,Stray Dogs - Italics,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,My coat is falling apart...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:19.15,Stray Dogs - Italics,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,A weathering ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.31,0:11:23.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot lose to one like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.25,0:11:26.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Margaret,0000,0000,0000,,who has never known defeat or humiliation!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.59,0:11:33.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Never known defeat, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.03,0:11:40.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Margaret!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.01,0:11:44.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Defeat and humiliation are always with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:54.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,I am a remnant, going through the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:11:59.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,As such, despair of this nature
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.19,0:12:00.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,will not ruin me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.34,0:12:12.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Not now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:14.98,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a wound caused \Nby The Scarlet Letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:19.14,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be... he was seriously \Ninjured when he came here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.14,0:12:21.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,This is nothing! Come at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.63,0:12:24.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Fight me with all you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.06,0:12:28.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, there was no \Npoint to me coming here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.30,0:12:31.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you go to such lengths?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.91,0:12:35.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,My only hope is for one word.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.09,0:12:38.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,A simple, trivial word \Nfrom a certain person...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.95,0:12:41.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of hearing that word,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.39,0:12:46.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,I have come through countless \Nhumiliating defeats!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.19,0:12:50.58,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,This man is a ruthless \Nkiller from the Port Mafia,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.22,0:12:54.01,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,yet at the same time, \Nhe longs deeply for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:57.75,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Something worth giving his life for...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.75,0:13:01.46,Stray Dogs - Italics,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,And with an intensity that nearly \Nrivals that of religious faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.27,0:13:06.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,You asked me to fight with all I've got, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:13.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,I've changed my mind. I will grant your wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.70,0:13:19.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.76,0:13:49.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Rashoumon...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.70,0:13:52.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,Jaws of Endless Gates!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.56,0:13:52.43,sign_19938_196_Jaws_of_Endless_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Jaws of Endless Gates
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.43,0:14:06.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Nathaniel,0000,0000,0000,,Margaret...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:27.55,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,People need to be told they're worthy \Nof being alive by someone else, or they can't go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:30.59,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you understand such a simple thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.85,0:14:34.89,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Those words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.30,0:14:38.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need you to tell \Nme that. I already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:42.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I'm so bored!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:44.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna go outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.97,0:14:47.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing out of the ordinary in the footage?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.49,0:14:49.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,Just a bunch of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:52.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to get into this hall
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.36,0:14:55.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,is through the underground railroad tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.61,0:14:58.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the enemy does try to enter,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.95,0:15:03.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,the security camera footage will \Ntell us before they get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.29,0:15:06.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,And there are lots of \Ntraps along the way, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.41,0:15:08.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,War is so boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.08,0:15:12.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,My emergency snacks ran out in half a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:15.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.66,0:15:18.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yosano-san, let's play hanafuda on this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.12,0:15:19.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What are we going to bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.18,0:15:26.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,Attacking enemy bases always \Nmakes my heart dance with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:29.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for the next move. \NHow go the preparations?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.92,0:15:31.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.50,0:15:35.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,You have more than enough force to \Ncrush the Armed Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.11,0:15:38.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to hearing a superb melody.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.40,0:15:40.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.69,0:15:43.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,President, I think we should \Ncall back the defensive teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.53,0:15:45.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.28,0:15:48.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,How many are attacking?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:53.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,One.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.94,0:16:05.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,Mii-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.32,0:16:10.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as this whole mess is over, \NI'll come for you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.35,0:16:13.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,N-N-Naomi-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.02,0:16:13.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Haruno-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:15.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,I-I-I was working! Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.68,0:16:18.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,We office workers are \Npart of the company, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:21.54,sign_23515_234_Tokyo_Daily_News,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo Daily News
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:21.54,sign_23515_235_40_killed__300__,Text,0000,0000,0000,,40 Killed, 300+ Injured in Cruise Liner \NExplosion at Yokohama Commercial Port
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:27.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,An explosion on a cruise liner \Nat a commercial port in Yokohama?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.12,0:16:30.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the Guild's ship, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:32.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Then what caused the explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.58,0:16:36.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,It was the other enemy,\Nthe one who loves explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.97,0:16:39.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,The Agency may be his next target...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.28,0:16:42.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,I hope my brother is safe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.61,0:16:47.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Naomi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.71,0:16:51.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,We know Mii-chan is okay, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.20,0:16:52.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Kirako,0000,0000,0000,,Please forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.79,0:16:58.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,Cameras 3, 4, and 8 have stopped transmitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.82,0:17:00.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Activate the automatic turrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:15.92,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,You'd send these puppets \Nto receive a special envoy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.92,0:17:17.68,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,You're so short-staffed, I could cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:20.04,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Could you send out something\Nthat's actually alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:21.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,President...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.39,0:17:26.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you of the same opinion as I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.14,0:17:34.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.62,0:17:36.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Only two?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:40.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,If you're dissatisfied with your reception, \Ncome back after making an appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.43,0:17:44.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,You think the Mafia needs an appointment \Nto raise hell in an enemy base?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.68,0:17:46.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I don't think they do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:49.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to raise hell, have at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.82,0:17:52.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not what you came here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.68,0:17:53.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.53,0:17:55.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.75,0:17:57.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,We're a detective agency, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.90,0:18:01.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,What good would we be if we couldn't figure \Nout a client's intentions at a glance?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.09,0:18:04.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your president?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.76,0:18:06.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.77,0:18:11.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a present from my boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.67,0:18:13.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Those are...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.46,0:18:16.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Members of the Guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.13,0:18:18.11,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,We reeled them in with bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.11,0:18:21.53,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,The time and location they'll \Nappear is written here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.98,0:18:24.16,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get many chances like this, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.69,0:18:27.63,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,You can get one over on \Nthat detestable Guild!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.56,0:18:35.25,Stray Dogs - Italics,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,The chance to ambush gifted Guild \Nmembers is indeed attractive...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:39.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's a titillating proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.21,0:18:40.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.23,0:18:42.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,But I've got an even better one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.89,0:18:45.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,How about I hack off your limbs
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.56,0:18:48.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,and make you cough up your plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:51.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Now that's a brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.18,0:18:53.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:54.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,Kenji!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.23,0:18:55.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.51,0:19:00.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Hi-yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.79,0:19:01.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.46,0:19:04.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.30,0:19:09.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,This is exactly what a job ought to be like!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.65,0:19:16.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.22,0:19:20.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,That ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.00,0:19:22.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Akiko,0000,0000,0000,,You're Nakahara Chuuya, the \Ngravity manipulator, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:25.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,That damn Dazai must have blabbed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:28.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,He's standing upside-down,\Nbut his hat isn't falling off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.28,0:19:31.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,City folk really are amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:38.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.95,0:19:42.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Who wants to fight against gravity?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.55,0:19:49.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Here's my answer, special \Nenvoy of the Port Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.34,0:19:50.46,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.46,0:19:52.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that if the Detective \NAgency defeats the Guild,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.23,0:19:56.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,you will slash the enemy's strength \Nwithout lifting a finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.90,0:20:01.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,If you're lucky, the Detective Agency and \Nthe Guild might even take each other out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:04.78,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,But you have nothing to lose yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.39,0:20:06.18,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.50,0:20:08.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,If what you say is true, then yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:10.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.95,0:20:12.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,What are you hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.66,0:20:13.64,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.07,0:20:17.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,What action is the Port Mafia going to take?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.35,0:20:20.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have to take any action.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.94,0:20:26.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.70,0:20:31.68,Stray Dogs - Italics,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild must have suspected \Na trap, just like we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:34.63,Stray Dogs - Italics,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,But they fell for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:38.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Because the bait was just too appetizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.62,0:20:40.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,What did you use to bait the Guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.03,0:20:47.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Steinbeck,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what nation you're in, \Nbeing in the countryside soothes the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.67,0:20:51.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Steinbeck,0000,0000,0000,,So, the Port Mafia's gift is just ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.46,0:20:56.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Lovecraft,0000,0000,0000,,This is obviously a trap to \Nlure us out. Why should we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.53,0:20:58.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Steinbeck,0000,0000,0000,,Because the bait's so appealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.33,0:21:00.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Steinbeck,0000,0000,0000,,If we succeed in the abduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.82,0:21:03.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Steinbeck,0000,0000,0000,,we've basically defeated \Nthe Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.95,0:21:05.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,You used our office staff as bait?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:08.67,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,You can still get them out of there in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.67,0:21:12.29,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, the Guild has no idea \Nthat you're about to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:13.91,Stray Dogs - Italics,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be an easy win.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.49,0:21:16.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is anything he's said untrue?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.22,0:21:19.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No, unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:24.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Times like these are when the \Ntruth is the most effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.50,0:21:31.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,"Even if they know it's a pitfall, \Nthe Agency will still fall right into it."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:34.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,My boss's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.15,0:21:37.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Order the office staff \Nto evacuate immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.96,0:21:39.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.90,0:21:43.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Yukichi,0000,0000,0000,,Put me through to Kunikida.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.10,0:23:18.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Doppo,0000,0000,0000,,We're the only ones who \Ncan get to them in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.89,0:23:20.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Doppo,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.35,0:23:23.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Doppo,0000,0000,0000,,Right. We'll head straight there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.47,0:23:29.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,The president?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.29,0:23:31.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Doppo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.69,0:23:33.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,What'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.97,0:23:40.27,sign_33950_337_Episode_Nineteen,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Nineteen \NWill of {\c&H0B0BB1&}Ty{\c&H000000&}coon
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.80,0:23:38.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Doppo,0000,0000,0000,,We're going head-to-head with the Guild.
